    "name": "NAICS Lookup API (Local dev)",
    "description": "Search 2022 6-digit NAICS codes by keyword. Returns top matches ranked by relevance.\n\n## Prerequisites\n\n- Python 3.10 or later\n    \n- The file `2022 NAICS Codes.xlsx` in the project folder.\n    \n    - Can be downladed at [https://www.naics.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/2022-NAICS-Codes-listed-numerically-2-Digit-through-6-Digit.xlsx](https://www.naics.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/2022-NAICS-Codes-listed-numerically-2-Digit-through-6-Digit.xlsx).\n        \n\n## How to Run the Server\n\n**Step 1 — Open a terminal and navigate to the project folder:**\n\n```\ncd \"C:\\Users\\{{your_username}}\\Desktop\\NAICS Lookup API\"\n\n ```\n\n**Step 2 — Install dependencies (first time only):**\n\n```\npip install -r requirements.txt\n\n ```\n\n**Step 3 — Start the server from cmd:**\n\n```\npython -m uvicorn main:app --reload\n\n ```\n\nYou should see:\n\n```\nINFO: Loaded 1012 NAICS records from 2022 NAICS Codes.xlsx\nINFO: Uvicorn running on http://127.0.0.1:8000\n\n ```\n\n**Step 4 — Confirm it is running:**\n\nOpen [http://localhost:8000/health](http://localhost:8000/health) in your browser. You should see:\n\n``` json\n{ \"status\": \"ok\", \"records_loaded\": 1012 }\n\n ```\n\nThe server is now ready. Run requests from this collection against `{{baseUrl}}` (default: [http://localhost:8000](http://localhost:8000)).\n\n## Stopping the Server\n\nPress `Ctrl + C` in the terminal.\n\n## Notes\n\n- `--reload` automatically restarts the server when you save changes to main.py. Remove it for production use.\n    \n- To use a different port: `uvicorn main:app --port 8080`\n    \n- To run from a different directory, set the data file path: `set NAICS_DATA_PATH=C:\\full\\path\\to\\2022 NAICS Codes.xlsx`",
